First, assume that $x \ge 0$ and $y \ge 0.$  If $y \ge x,$ then
\[|x + y| + |x - y| = x + y + y - x = 2y \le 4,\]so $y \le 2.$  If $y < x,$ then
\[|x + y| + |x - y| = x + y + x - y = 2x \le 4,\]so $x \le 2.$

Thus, the portion of the graph in the first quadrant is as follows:

[asy]
